TY  - JOUR
T1  - Growth, Trade, and Inequality
AU  - Grossman, Gene M.
AU  - Helpman, Elhanan
Y1  - 2018/01/01
PY  - 2018
DA  - 2018/01/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA14518
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
JA  - Econometrica
SP  - 37
EP  - 83
VL  - 86
IS  - 1
KW  - Endogenous growth
KW  - innovation
KW  - income distribution
KW  - income inequality
KW  - trade and growth
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA14518
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We introduce firm and worker heterogeneity into a model of innovation-driven endogenous growth. Individuals who differ in ability sort into either a research activity or a manufacturing sector. Research projects generate new varieties of a differentiated product. Projects differ in quality and the resulting technologies differ in productivity. In both sectors, there is a complementarity between firm quality and worker ability. We study the co-determination of growth and income inequality in both the closed and open economy, as well as the spillover effects of policy in one country to outcomes in others.
ER  - 

