TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Dual Approach to Recursive Optimization: Theory and Examples
AU  - Pavoni, Nicola
AU  - Sleet, Christopher
AU  - Messner, Matthias
Y1  - 2018/01/01
PY  - 2018
DA  - 2018/01/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA11905
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
JA  - Econometrica
SP  - 133
EP  - 172
VL  - 86
IS  - 1
KW  - Dynamic contracts
KW  - duality
KW  - dynamic programming
KW  - contraction mapping
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA11905
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We develop a recursive dual method for solving dynamic economic problems. The method uses a Lagrangian to pair a dynamic recursive economic problem with a dual problem. We show that such dual problems can be recursively decomposed with costates (i.e., Lagrange multipliers on laws of motion) functioning as state variables. In dynamic contracting and policy settings, the method often replaces an endogenous state space of forward-looking utilities with an exogenously given state space of costates. We provide a principle of optimality for dual problems and give conditions under which the dual Bellman operator is a contraction with the optimal dual value function its unique fixed point. We relate economic problems to their duals, address computational issues, and give examples.
ER  - 

